(firstQuint)Electronic Cigarette Use and Quitting in Youth.

 Subjects are from a cohort of Youth Quitline callers and smoking youth (N=200) in Hong Kong.

 The longitudinal study will investigate the effects of baseline e-cigarette use on quitting (including relapse), nicotine addiction and intention to smoke at 12-month telephone follow-up.

 A qualitative study will be conducted on 10 ex- and 10 current smokers to supplement and facilitate interpretation of the quantitative findings.

